theorem
Th36: (R is (Congruence of X) iff (R is (R-congruence of X) & R is (L-congruence of X)))
proof
A1: ( field R ) = (the carrier of X) by EQREL_1:9;
then A2: R is_reflexive_in (the carrier of X) by RELAT_2:def 9;
thus (R is (Congruence of X) implies (R is (R-congruence of X) & R is (L-congruence of X)))
proof
assume A3: R is (Congruence of X);
thus R is (R-congruence of X)
proof
let x being (Element of X),y being (Element of X);
assume A4: [ x,y ] in R;
let u being (Element of X);
[ u,u ] in R by A2,RELAT_2:def 1;
hence thesis by A3,A4,CKB50:def 1;
end;

let x being (Element of X),y being (Element of X);
assume A5: [ x,y ] in R;
let u being (Element of X);
[ u,u ] in R by A2,RELAT_2:def 1;
hence thesis by A3,A5,CKB50:def 1;
end;

assume A6: (R is (R-congruence of X) & R is (L-congruence of X));
A7: R is_transitive_in (the carrier of X) by A1,RELAT_2:def 16;
now
let x being (Element of X),y being (Element of X),u being (Element of X),v being (Element of X);
assume ([ x,y ] in R & [ u,v ] in R);
then ([ ( x \ u ),( y \ u ) ] in R & [ ( y \ u ),( y \ v ) ] in R) by A6,CKB51:def 1,CKB52:def 1;
hence [ ( x \ u ),( y \ v ) ] in R by A7,RELAT_2:def 8;
end;
hence thesis by CKB50:def 1;
end;
